qualifications_minimum:
Ph.D in Anthropology (completed or in progress, preferably in Social Cultural Anthropology);
Strong background in medical anthropology;
Demonstrated evidence of superior teaching is required

qualifications_preferred:
2-3 years managing projects in an corporate setting;
familiarity with the Project Management Body Of Knowledge v8 and the Agile Practice Guide;
experience with the theory, tools and techniques used in Traditional Project Management and in Agile Project;
management either through work experience, completing courses or reviewing textbooks;
experience with case study analysis as a TA;
prior experience TAing a project management course; and
experience TAing a classes of 40-50 students with group and individual gradeable components.
